AB  - Condition monitoring of generators is essential to prevent potential failures that could interrupt power generation. By employing smart sensors connected through a network, it is possible to continuously monitor these devices and perform predictive maintenance based on their condition, thereby minimizing the risk of equipment breakdown. This paper presents the development of an IoT-based system designed for a hydroelectric power plant, composed of two main components: a smart sensor for detecting mechanical faults in a motor through vibration analysis, and a smart sensor for estimating the water level in a reservoir. A vibrometer and an ultrasonic level sensor are employed for these tasks. The acquired data are transmitted via LoRa to the control unit. The system was successfully implemented, and the data are transmitted through LoRaWAN to the platform The Things Network.
