AB  - This paper proposes an intelligent fault diagnosis method for hydropower units based on a time-series Transformer. The method integrates vibration, electrical, and hydraulic monitoring data, and employs a multi-head self-attention mechanism to capture global features and temporal dependencies. Experimental results show that the proposed model outperforms traditional deep learning methods in accuracy, F1-score, and AUC. In addition, robustness tests under noise interference and variable load conditions demonstrate that the model maintains stable performance, confirming its adaptability to complex and dynamic operating environments. The proposed approach provides an effective framework for the intelligent operation, maintenance, and health management of hydropower units.
