AB  - With the rapid advancement of hydroelectric power stations, an increasing array of power equipment has been deployed. To maintain these assets in optimal operating condition, advanced portable detection methods have been adopted, including infrared imaging, partial discharge analysis, and earthing current measurement. These techniques have played a crucial role in enhancing the reliability of electricity in power plants. However, numerous challenges have arisen, including complex operations, substantial labor requirements, and limited analytical capabilities. To address these issues, this paper proposes an intelligent management system for live detection data. Initially, an application for mobile devices has been developed to interface with portable detection devices via Wi-Fi, This application automatically collects live data in a predefined format, including but not limited to infrared images,PD,PRPD and temperature. This significantly streamlines the process of data accumulation and cleaning, saving considerable time. Subsequently, an information management system has been developed on a server to store and manage this live data. Within this system, various analytical functions such as comparative analysis, data statistics, and association analysis are employed to enhance the level of data utilization. Building upon the established information system, this paper introduces the use of case-based reasoning for fault diagnosis in power transformers. Over 245 faulty instances have been compiled from 50 hydroelectric power stations and cataloged in a case base. KNN algorithm is employed to identify and recommend the most closely matched cases within this repository. Upon evaluation, the accuracy of this case-based reasoning approach has been found to reach 90%, demonstrating its potential as an effective diagnostic tool. The proposed information management system has been effectively implemented in numerous hydro power stations throughout Hunan Province, China. It has enabled deep analysis of live detection data, significantly enhancing the safety and operational reliability of power equipment in these facilities.
ER  - 

