AB  - Aiming at the problem that traditional models cannot accurately predict, a method for predicting the vibration trend of hydropower units based on an improved deep belief network is proposed. Firstly, we can use variational mode decomposition to process vibration signals. Then, feature extraction is performed on the processed signal, and a sparrow search algorithm is used to improve the diagnostic model. Finally, a multi-step prediction model combining variational mode decomposition and deep belief network was proposed to achieve the prediction of vibration trends. The results indicate that the prediction model has high accuracy, good prediction performance, and rich reference value.
